de.feig.FEDM.Core.TagHandler

Class TH_Base

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.feig.FEDM.Core.TagHandler.TH_Base
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    TH_EPC_Class1_Gen2, TH_ISO14443, TH_ISO15693

    public class TH_Base
extends java.lang.Object
    Base class for transponder.


    Description:
    High-level class for easy-to-use Transponder specific communication. See ITagGroup for additional information.
    This class supports non-addressed, selected and addressed mode in Host-Mode

      • readMultipleBlocks

        public int readMultipleBlocks(int firstDataBlock,
                              int noOfDataBlocks,
                              TH_Result result)
                       throws FeException
        Read of transponder data.
        Parameters:
        firstDataBlock - first data block address
        noOfDataBlocks - number of requested data blocks
        result - TH_Result object containing return values
        Returns:
        operation status
        • 0 if OK
        • > 0 status byte of the responded protocol, if the Reader signals a problem. See Reader's System Manual for the full list with all status bytes
        Throws:
        FeException - exception with error code (<0)
        Description:
        Basic [0xB0][0x23] Read Multiple Blocks command
        - Without support for extended address mode
        - Without request of security status

        The result object of type TH_Result contains only valid data (result.blockSize and result.data), if the operation status is 0.

      • readMultipleBlocksWithSecStatus

        public int readMultipleBlocksWithSecStatus(int firstDataBlock,
                                           int noOfDataBlocks,
                                           TH_Result result)
                                    throws FeException
        Read of transponder data with additional security status.
        Parameters:
        firstDataBlock - first data block address
        noOfDataBlocks - number of requested data blocks
        result - TH_Result object containing return values
        Returns:
        operation status
        • 0 if OK
        • > 0 status byte of the responded protocol, if the Reader signals a problem. See Reader's System Manual for the full list with all status bytes
        Throws:
        FeException - exception with error code (<0)
        Description:
        Basic [0xB0][0x23] Read Multiple Blocks command with additional security status
        - Without support for extended address mode

        The result object of type "TH_Result" contains only valid data (result.blockSize, result.data and result.securityStatus), if the operation status is 0.

      • writeMultipleBlocks

        public int writeMultipleBlocks(int firstDataBlock,
                               int noOfDataBlocks,
                               int blockSize,
                               byte[] data)
                        throws FeException
        Write of transponder data.
        Parameters:
        firstDataBlock - first data block address
        noOfDataBlocks - number of requested data blocks
        blockSize - number of bytes in each data block
        data - byte array with transponder data to be written to
        Returns:
        operation status
        • 0 if OK
        • > 0 status byte of the responded protocol, if the Reader signals a problem. See Reader's System Manual for the full list with all status bytes
        Throws:
        FeException - exception with error code (<0)
        Description:
        Basic [0xB0][0x24] Write Multiple Blocks command
        - Without support for extended address mode

        If the return status is 0x03, the errorDBAddress is set.
